raw_data.title: IT Consulting Engineer
raw_data.description: Provide customers technical leadership in the design, installation, configuration, and implementation of OEM products and services. Help document best practices in developing and deploying OEM solutions. Responsibilities: Independently conduct enterprise engagements with customers; maintain current knowledge of OEM products and IT services; document best practices in developing and deploying OEM solutions. Requirements: Relevant experience, including customer-facing and IT consulting experience with public and government sector highly desired; strong technical knowledge of one or more Commvault Simpana suite; 4+ years of experience in infrastructure architecture and design of complex distributed system environments, including failover techniques, recovery/rollback and application partitioning, understanding of storage architectures, including peripherals interfaces (SCSI, RAID, Ethernet) and multi-processor designs (SMP), 4+ years’ experience virtualizing enterprise applications (Exchange, SQL, ORACLE, Web servers, etc.).
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: PhD + 0 years relevant experience, or Master’s + 2 years relevant experience, or Associate’s + 6 years relevant experience, or High School + 8 years relevant experience
